IPSync (V 1.0) 
	About
		A suite of tools used to keep track of a notify users of changes in their public ip address
		Created by Ian Baldwin <iantbaldwin@elektrikfish.com> on 11/18/2014
	
	Usage
		At the moment, the program exists only as a singular shell script and only keep track of 'local' (read public IP of network)
		IP address. Notifications only occur when the script is run, currently.
	
	Future Plans
		-Convert program to daemon so it can constatly watch for changes
		-Sync the IP database between client servers
		-Provide suite of notification scripts to notify users of changes remotely
		-Interface with DNS servers to change A records to keep servers hosted on network with dyanmic IP address downtime to minumum 